At the end of an interview, a more polished and professional way to say "It was great talking with you" could be:

Professional & Polite Variations:
It was great talking with you

Thanks for this opportunity and it was a nice talking with you.

“It was a pleasure speaking with you today.”

“I really enjoyed our conversation—thank you for your time.”

“Thank you for the insightful conversation. It was great speaking with you.”

“I appreciate the opportunity to speak with you—it’s been a great discussion.”

“It was a very engaging discussion. Thank you again for your time.”

If You Want to Add a Strong Closing Note:
“I’m excited about the possibility of joining your team. It was great speaking with you.”

“Thanks again for this opportunity. I really enjoyed learning more about the role and the team.”